{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"1464270688850918615","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2011-11-14T02:30:00-08:00","updated":"2011-11-14T02:30:01-08:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2011/11/pomegranates.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/1464270688850918615","title":"Pomegranates!","content":"<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-h_47pYj8Zn0/TsCdHLnbWEI/AAAAAAAAJt8/sQCAT_1vL4c/s1600/pomegranate+seeds.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-h_47pYj8Zn0/TsCdHLnbWEI/AAAAAAAAJt8/sQCAT_1vL4c/s1600/pomegranate+seeds.jpg\" /></a></div>It's pomegranate season! I loved pomegranates as a kid because the seeds inside reminded me of lost treasure â€” all these glistening rubies just waiting to be found. Nowadays, I love them because they remind me of the holidays. Using the seeds to make festive ice cubes is one of my favorite party tricks.<br />\n<br />\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-7XAtFwQ_qXw/TsCdLWvoNBI/AAAAAAAAJuE/sAOuRT1KsZs/s1600/pomegranate+ice+cubes.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-7XAtFwQ_qXw/TsCdLWvoNBI/AAAAAAAAJuE/sAOuRT1KsZs/s1600/pomegranate+ice+cubes.jpg\" /></a></div><br />\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-En9VEYU_ZHo/TsCdQErAbGI/AAAAAAAAJuU/gWbqFIIH7MY/s1600/pom+cubes2.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-En9VEYU_ZHo/TsCdQErAbGI/AAAAAAAAJuU/gWbqFIIH7MY/s1600/pom+cubes2.jpg\" /></a></div><br />\nUsing a sharp knife, cut a pomegranate in half from top to bottom and then use your hands to carefully pick out all the seeds. (Tip: Don't wear a white shirt!) Drop a few seeds in each ice cube compartment, fill with water, and freeze. Even a simple glass of water looks like it's ready to have a good time :)<br />\n<br />\nAnd two other pomegranate party ideas I love:<br />\n<br />\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-zFBxKTPTgCk/TsCdR6CasSI/AAAAAAAAJuc/Fk8wB_qIvuY/s1600/pomegranate-place-card.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-zFBxKTPTgCk/TsCdR6CasSI/AAAAAAAAJuc/Fk8wB_qIvuY/s1600/pomegranate-place-card.jpg\" /></a></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/uhIv0a\">Pomegranate place cards</a></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br />\n</div><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-HScCLlmWeJE/TsCdVUn7oPI/AAAAAAAAJuk/ICqgclDFui0/s1600/pomegranate+fontina+rice+balls.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"400\" src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-HScCLlmWeJE/TsCdVUn7oPI/AAAAAAAAJuk/ICqgclDFui0/s400/pomegranate+fontina+rice+balls.jpg\" width=\"320\" /></a></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/uC7smv\">Pomegranate-fontina rice balls</a>&nbsp;</div><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><br />\n</div>","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"2","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/1464270688850918615/comments"},"labels":["To Eat"]}